Amalgamated Telecom Holdings Limited Key Developments

Amalgamated Telecom Holdings Limited Reports Audited Consolidated and Parent Earnings Results for the Year Ended March 31, 2017
Jun 28 17
Amalgamated Telecom Holdings Limited reported audited consolidated and parent earnings results for the year ended March 31, 2017. For the year, on consolidated basis, the company reported revenue was FJD 394,702,000 against FJD 356,211,000 a year ago. Operating profit was FJD 108,411,000 against FJD 90,878,000 a year ago. Profit from operations was FJD 108,415,000 compared to FJD 91,559,000 a year ago. Profit before income tax was 108,556,000 against FJD 91,559,000 a year ago. Profit attributable to equity holders of the holding company was FJD 54,222,000 against FJD 56,725,000 a year ago. Basic and diluted earnings per share were 12.8 cents against 13.4 cents a year ago. Net cash inflows from operating activities were FJD 132,590,000 against FJD 105,006,000 a year ago. Payments for property, plant and equipment was FJD 53,033,000 against FJD 41,267,000 a year ago. Payments for intangible assets were FJD 1,135,000 against FJD 604,000 a year ago. Net debt was FJD 118,233,000 as on March 31, 2017 against FJD 12,139,000 as on March 31, 2016. 

For the year, on parent basis, the company reported revenue was FJD 42,679,000 against FJD 34,629,000 a year ago. Operating profit was FJD 42,170,000 against FJD 32,510,000 a year ago. Profit from operations was FJD 42,954,000 compared to FJD 34,420,000 a year ago. Profit before income tax was FJD 42,954,000 against FJD 34,420,000 a year ago. Profit attributable to equity holders of the holding company was FJD 42,703,000 against FJD 34,268,000 a year ago. Net cash inflows from operating activities were FJD 35,640,000 against FJD 35,865,000 a year ago. Payments for property, plant and equipment was FJD 27,000 compared to FJD 1,000 a year ago.


Amalgamated Telecom Holdings Appoints Ivan Fong as its Chief Executive Officer
Feb 24 17
Amalgamated Telecom Holdings (ATH) has confirmed Ivan Fong as its chief executive officer. Fong previously served as ATH general manager since January 2011.


Amalgamated Telecom Holdings Interim Dividend Financial Year Ending 31 March 2017, Payable on 23 March 2017
Feb 24 17
Amalgamated Telecom Holdings (ATH) has declared an interim dividend of 2 cents per share or a total FJD 8.4 million for its financial year ending 31 March 2017. Payment to ATH shareholders is scheduled for 23 March 2017.


